summary: This is a court order from Judge Alison J. Nathan in the Ghislaine Maxwell criminal case, regarding the third production of documents from the Epstein Victims' Compensation Program. The order permits the parties to review the materials under a protective order and directs the Administrator to produce them by a specific deadline.

persons.name: Ghislaine Maxwell
persons.context: The defendant in the criminal case referenced in the court order.

persons.name: Alison J. Nathan
persons.context: The judge issuing the order regarding the production of materials from the Epstein Victims' Compensation Program.

events.title: Court Order for Third Production from Victims' Program
events.description: Judge Alison J. Nathan orders the Administrator of the Epstein Victims' Compensation Program to produce a third set of materials to the parties in the Ghislaine Maxwell case under the provisions of a protective order.

keyFacts: The court received a third production of documents from the Epstein Victims' Compensation Program via a Rule 17(c) subpoena.
Judge Alison J. Nathan ordered that the parties in the Ghislaine Maxwell case could review these materials under an existing protective order.
The court explicitly stated it made no determination regarding the admissibility of any of the material.
The Administrator of the Epstein Victims' Compensation Program was ordered to produce the materials to the parties by 8:30 p.m. on November 28, 2021.
